At Smile Foundation’s education centre in Jugibari, Assam, children from the Mising community are discovering the joy of learning—many for the first time. 

Among them is Antora, whose father dreams big for her, believing education can open doors no one in their family has walked through. While the Mising tribe is known for its warmth, culture and togetherness, opportunities like this are rare. The centre is a space of hope—where teachers patiently guide every child, turning classrooms into places of imagination and confidence.

Join hands in ensuring #ShikshaNaRuke for every child, please visit: https://donate.smilefoundationindia.org/donate-for-education/

Colloquium VI | Spotlight on Community-Led Innovation

The 6th edition of Smile Foundation’s Colloquium, in association with Change the Game Academy, concluded on an inspiring note, bringing together a powerful panel of thought leaders and changemakers to exchange ideas on “Innovative Community Practices of CBOs for Building Resilient Communities.”

From grassroots champions to corporate voices, Colloquium VI became a vibrant space for dialogue, collaboration, and actionable insights. The discussions underscored the vital role of Community-Based Organizations (CBOs) in creating sustainable, inclusive change - through local leadership, contextual solutions, and cross-sector partnerships.

Each speaker brought a unique lens to the table, reaffirming our shared belief - that resilient communities are built when local organizations are empowered to lead.

Since 2007, Smile Foundation, as the nodal partner for Asia under the Change the Game Academy, has worked to strengthen grassroots leadership across 16 countries. Colloquium VI is a reflection of this ongoing commitment.

Thank you to all our speakers, partners, and participants for making this edition impactful and future-focused.

🔗 Learn more about Empowering Grassroots: https://www.smilefoundationindia.org/ctgi/

#ColloquiumVI #SmileFoundation #CTGA #EmpoweringGrassroots #CommunityLeadership #CivicEngagement #SocialImpact #DevelopmentDialogue

latestPosts.caption:
Strengthening Women’s Health and Nutrition in Chakan, Pune

Smile Foundation has joined hands with Thermo Fisher Scientific under the Pink Smile initiative to provide doorstep healthcare to underserved communities in Chakan, Pune. Through a dedicated Mobile Medical Unit, the initiative will reach around 45,000 women, children, and adolescents across 20 anganwadis, with a sharp focus on maternal and child health, nutrition, and preventive care.

The Pink Smile Van was flagged off in the presence of Mr. Krishna Murthy (GM, Thermo Fisher Scientific), Shri Palkar (CDPO), Smt. Sharmila Pati (Anganwadi Supervisor), Smita (CHO, Sub Centre), and other local stakeholders.

The programme offers a comprehensive range of services including general health check-ups, NCD screenings, anaemia control, gynaecology and paediatric teleconsultations, and structured awareness sessions on menstrual hygiene, nutrition, reproductive health, and sanitation. Cases of severe anaemia and malnutrition are referred for specialised OPD care with regular follow-ups to ensure sustained impact.

Aligned with national missions such as Anaemia Mukt Bharat, the initiative reinforces our collective commitment towards building a Kuposhan Mukt Bharat.

We thank Thermo Fisher Scientific for partnering with us to bring quality healthcare closer to those who need it most.

latestPosts.caption:
“Every time I see Mishita with her books and colours, I feel a small sense of joy.

We live a simple life in Medinipur. My husband runs a small shop, and I take care of the house. Life has had its challenges, but Mishita gives us something to look forward to.

She has always enjoyed studying. Now she does well in school and often comes first in her class. I remember how happy she was when she brought home her report card. She also loves painting. Her drawings reflect the things she notices around her. One day she told me she wants to become a teacher. I may not understand all that she studies, but I can see how much it matters to her.”

Mishita’s mother

Mishita (name changed) studies at Smile Foundation’s Mission Education centre in Medinipur, West Bengal.

To join hands in ensuring #ShikshaNaRuke for any child, please visit: https://donate.smilefoundationindia.org/donate-for-education

“It wasn’t easy watching my father work so hard alone. But things changed when I joined Smile Foundation’s skill and employability training. I learned, grew and found the strength to support him.

Today, I proudly stand beside my father, not behind him. I help my family, and that feeling is beyond words. This training didn’t just give me skills—it gave me hope, confidence, and a chance to change our life.”

Yash Kumar
(Trained and Placed)

To join hands in our efforts, please visit: https://donate.smilefoundationindia.org/donate-for-livelihood/

#TayyariKalKi

"At Smile Foundation, working with technology is about making things simpler, quicker, and more meaningful for the people we serve.

With 16 years of experience in the tech world, I have come to believe that when a team understands the need to grow with technology, real and lasting change becomes possible. Whether it is streamlining our processes, moving systems online, or making information easier to access, we have made changes that help us work more smoothly every day.

What I value most is that, as a team, we have adopted technology with thought and care, always keeping people and purpose at the centre. These improvements have allowed our teams in the field to focus more on supporting children and communities, without being held back by delays or outdated systems.

I feel grateful to be part of a team that embraces change, supports one another, and keeps looking for better ways to serve - with clarity, confidence, and heart."

Irteza Hussain
IT Team, Smile Foundation

#GreatPlaceToWork #Smilians #EmployeeSpeak
